            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p><g ref="cross">+</g> ἐτέλεσεν <lb/>τὸν δρόμον <lb/>καὶ ἐνθάδε <lb/>κατετήθη ὁ
                            <lb/><expan><abbr>τρισμακάρ</abbr><ex>ιος</ex></expan>
                    <lb/>Ἰωάννης <lb/>Στεφάνου
                        <expan><abbr>πρ</abbr><ex>εσβύτερος</ex></expan><lb/><expan><abbr>μ</abbr><ex>ηνὶ</ex></expan>
                        Ἀπελ<supplied reason="omitted">λ</supplied>αίου <num>κʹ</num>
                    <lb/><expan><abbr>ἰνδ</abbr><ex>ικτιῶνος</ex></expan>
                    <num>γʹ</num> ἔτους <lb/><num>φθʹ</num>
                    <expan><abbr>δουλεύσ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan>
                    <lb/>τῇ
                        <expan><abbr>ἐκ</abbr><ex>κ</ex><abbr>λησ</abbr><ex>ίᾳ</ex></expan> ἐν
                            <expan><abbr>Χ</abbr><ex>ριστ</ex><abbr>ῷ</abbr></expan>. </p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>+ Completed the race, and here was laid thrice blessed John (son) of Stephan,
                    priest, on the 20th of the month of Apellaius, in the 3rd indiction-year, in the
                    eyar 509. Having served the Church in Christ.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The phrase from the first two lines comes from 1 Tim 4:7. The final line uses
                    phrasing from 1 Cor 1:2, 1 Cor 10:12, Gal 1:13, 1 Thes 2:14.</p>
            </div>
